<h1 class="doc-page-title">Delivery reporting</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">Comprehensive guide to tracking and reporting on product delivery, performance metrics, and compliance across the DfE digital portfolio.</p>

<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

<p>Delivery reporting in COMPASS enables you to track, monitor, and report on the delivery of products and services across the Department for Education. This includes project delivery, operational performance, compliance tracking, and strategic alignment.</p>

<div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card border-primary h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-project-diagram text-primary"></i> Project delivery</h3>
                <p class="small">Track project lifecycle, milestones, deliverables, outcomes, and dependencies for delivery programmes and projects.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card border-success h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-chart-line text-success"></i> Operational performance</h3>
                <p class="small">Monitor product performance metrics, track against targets, and visualise trends over time.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card border-info h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-check text-info"></i> Compliance tracking</h3>
                <p class="small">Conduct functional standards assessments, track compliance progress, and demonstrate adherence to DDaT standards.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card border-warning h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-bullseye text-warning"></i> Strategic alignment</h3>
                <p class="small">Link products and projects to strategic objectives, track progress, and demonstrate strategic value.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="projects">Project delivery</h2>

<p>The project delivery system helps you manage and track delivery programmes and projects from initiation through to completion.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Key features:</h3>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="h6">Project management</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Project creation:</strong> Set up new projects with comprehensive details including name, description, phase, and status</li>
            <li><strong>RAG tracking:</strong> Monitor red-amber-green status for delivery, cost, and resource dimensions</li>
            <li><strong>Milestone tracking:</strong> Track key milestones with dates, statuses, and progress</li>
            <li><strong>Deliverable management:</strong> Define and track project deliverables</li>
            <li><strong>Outcome tracking:</strong> Document and monitor project outcomes with success measures</li>
            <li><strong>Success recording:</strong> Capture successes and wins throughout the project lifecycle</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="h6">Programme oversight</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Dependencies:</strong> Track internal and external dependencies with status and impact</li>
            <li><strong>Issues log:</strong> Manage project issues separate from operational issues</li>
            <li><strong>Product linking:</strong> Associate products with projects and track relationships</li>
            <li><strong>Strategic alignment:</strong> Link projects to strategic objectives</li>
            <li><strong>Funding tracking:</strong> Monitor project funding sources and amounts</li>
            <li><strong>Contact management:</strong> Assign project roles (Project Manager, SRO, Delivery Manager, etc.)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating and managing projects:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Delivery reporting</strong> in the main navigation</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create new project</strong></li>
    <li>Complete the project form with:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Basic information:</strong> Name, description, objectives, and expected benefits</li>
            <li><strong>Dates:</strong> Start date, planned end date, and actual end date (when complete)</li>
            <li><strong>Phase and status:</strong> Select current phase (discovery, alpha, beta, live) and status</li>
            <li><strong>RAG status:</strong> Set red-amber-green indicators for delivery, cost, and resource</li>
            <li><strong>Funding:</strong> Add funding sources and amounts</li>
            <li><strong>Contacts:</strong> Assign key roles and team members</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Use the tabbed interface to manage different aspects:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Overview:</strong> Project summary and RAG tracking</li>
            <li><strong>Milestones:</strong> Track key deliverable dates</li>
            <li><strong>Deliverables:</strong> Manage project deliverables</li>
            <li><strong>Outcomes:</strong> Define and track outcomes</li>
            <li><strong>Products:</strong> Link associated products</li>
            <li><strong>Dependencies:</strong> Manage dependencies</li>
            <li><strong>Issues:</strong> Track project issues</li>
            <li><strong>Successes:</strong> Record wins and achievements</li>
            <li><strong>Strategic alignment:</strong> Link to strategic objectives</li>
            <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Manage funding and contacts</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Best practice:</strong> Update RAG status weekly and add commentary explaining any status changes. This provides valuable context for portfolio reviews and helps identify trends.</p>
</div>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Project filtering and views:</h3>

<p>The project index provides powerful filtering to help you find and analyse projects:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Phase filters:</strong> Filter by discovery, alpha, beta, live, or retired</li>
    <li><strong>Status filters:</strong> Filter by active, on hold, completed, or cancelled</li>
    <li><strong>RAG filters:</strong> Filter by delivery, cost, or resource RAG status</li>
    <li><strong>Strategic objective:</strong> Filter by linked strategic objectives</li>
    <li><strong>Funding source:</strong> Filter by funding source</li>
    <li><strong>Search:</strong> Full-text search across project names and descriptions</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="products">Product management</h2>

<p>Product management in COMPASS integrates with the FIPS CMS to provide real-time product information and comprehensive product dashboards.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product features:</h3>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="h6">Product catalogue</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Real-time sync:</strong> Product data is fetched directly from FIPS CMS API</li>
            <li><strong>Product search:</strong> Search by name, FIPS ID, or description</li>
            <li><strong>Product filtering:</strong> Filter by phase, status, business area, or technology</li>
            <li><strong>Product dashboards:</strong> Comprehensive view of each product</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="h6">Product tracking</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>RAID integration:</strong> View all risks, issues, actions, and milestones for each product</li>
            <li><strong>Performance metrics:</strong> Track product-specific performance metrics</li>
            <li><strong>Compliance tracking:</strong> Monitor functional standards assessments</li>
            <li><strong>Project linking:</strong> See which projects a product is associated with</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using product dashboards:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Products</strong> in the main navigation</li>
    <li>Find your product using search or filters</li>
    <li>Click on the product to view its dashboard</li>
    <li>The dashboard shows:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Product information:</strong> Phase, status, description, and contacts</li>
            <li><strong>RAID summary:</strong> Count and status of risks, issues, actions, and milestones</li>
            <li><strong>Performance metrics:</strong> Latest submitted metrics and trends</li>
            <li><strong>Compliance status:</strong> Functional standards assessment results</li>
            <li><strong>Strategic links:</strong> Connected strategic objectives</li>
            <li><strong>Related projects:</strong> Projects this product is part of</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Use quick action buttons to:
        <ul>
            <li>Submit performance metrics</li>
            <li>Create risks, issues, or actions for this product</li>
            <li>Conduct functional standards assessments</li>
            <li>View detailed reports</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Product information is cached for performance. If you've recently updated product details in FIPS CMS, it may take up to an hour to appear in COMPASS, or you can clear the cache from the administration area.</p>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="performance-metrics">Performance metrics</h2>

<p>Performance metrics enable you to track how well your products and services are performing against defined measures.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Metric types:</h3>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Product performance metrics</h4>
                <p class="small">Track product-specific performance measures:</p>
                <ul class="small mb-0">
                    <li>User satisfaction (percentage 0-100%)</li>
                    <li>Service availability/uptime (percentage 0-100%)</li>
                    <li>Transaction volumes (numbers)</li>
                    <li>Response times (decimals in milliseconds)</li>
                    <li>Error rates (percentage 0-100%)</li>
                    <li>Cost per transaction (decimals)</li>
                    <li>Custom product-specific metrics (text, numbers, decimals, or percentages)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="h6">Enterprise metrics</h4>
                <p class="small">Track enterprise-wide KPIs:</p>
                <ul class="small mb-0">
                    <li>Portfolio health indicators</li>
                    <li>Strategic objective progress</li>
                    <li>Resource utilisation</li>
                    <li>Budget tracking</li>
                    <li>Compliance metrics</li>
                    <li>Risk exposure measures</li>
                    <li>Custom enterprise metrics (text, numbers, decimals, or percentages)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Submitting performance metrics:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Product reporting → Performance metrics</strong></li>
    <li>Select your product</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit metrics</strong></li>
    <li>For each metric:
        <ul>
            <li>Enter the <strong>actual value</strong> (number, decimal, percentage, or text as appropriate)</li>
            <li>Enter the <strong>target value</strong> (if applicable)</li>
            <li>Select the <strong>reporting period</strong> (month/year or date range)</li>
            <li>Add <strong>notes or commentary</strong> to provide context</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing metric history and trends:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to your product's dashboard or the performance metrics page</li>
    <li>Click <strong>View history</strong> for a specific metric</li>
    <li>You'll see:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Line chart:</strong> Visualising metric values over time</li>
            <li><strong>Target comparison:</strong> Actual vs. target performance (if targets are set)</li>
            <li><strong>Historical table:</strong> All previous submissions with dates and values</li>
            <li><strong>Trend indicators:</strong> Up/down arrows showing direction of change</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Use date range filters to focus on specific time periods</li>
    <li>Export data to Excel for further analysis</li>
</ol>

<div class="card border-success mt-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb text-warning"></i> Metric submission best practices</h4>
        <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>Submit metrics on a regular schedule (monthly is typical)</li>
            <li>Be consistent with measurement methodology</li>
            <li>Always add commentary to explain significant changes</li>
            <li>Set realistic targets based on historical performance</li>
            <li>Review trends regularly to identify patterns</li>
            <li>If you can't provide a metric, explain why in the notes</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="enterprise-metrics">Enterprise metrics</h2>

<p>Enterprise metrics provide high-level visibility of portfolio-wide performance and strategic progress.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enterprise metrics dashboard:</h3>

<p>The enterprise metrics dashboard provides an executive view of:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Strategic objective progress:</strong> Track progress towards strategic goals</li>
    <li><strong>Portfolio health:</strong> Overall health indicators across all products</li>
    <li><strong>Resource utilisation:</strong> Budget, staff, and capacity metrics</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance status:</strong> Overall compliance with standards and policies</li>
    <li><strong>Risk exposure:</strong> Enterprise-level risk profile</li>
    <li><strong>Custom KPIs:</strong> Configurable enterprise-wide key performance indicators</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Submitting enterprise metrics:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Enterprise metrics</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit metrics</strong></li>
    <li>Complete the enterprise metrics form with:
        <ul>
            <li>Metric values (text, numbers, decimals, or percentages based on metric definition)</li>
            <li>Reporting period</li>
            <li>Commentary and context</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong></li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> <strong>Note:</strong> Enterprise metrics are typically managed by senior leadership or portfolio management teams. Access may be restricted based on your role.</p>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="functional-standards">Functional standards compliance</h2>

<p>COMPASS supports comprehensive tracking of DDaT functional standards compliance across your product portfolio.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Standards framework:</h3>

<p>The functional standards framework in COMPASS includes:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Standards library:</strong> Complete catalogue of DDaT functional standards</li>
    <li><strong>Themes:</strong> Standards organised by theme (e.g., agile delivery, user research, technology)</li>
    <li><strong>Practice areas:</strong> Further categorisation within themes</li>
    <li><strong>Criteria:</strong> Specific criteria for each standard with detailed descriptions</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Conducting a functional standards assessment:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Functional standards</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Conduct assessment</strong></li>
    <li>Select:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Product:</strong> The product being assessed</li>
            <li><strong>Standard:</strong> The functional standard to assess against</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Begin assessment</strong></li>
    <li>For each criterion in the standard:
        <ul>
            <li>Read the criterion description carefully</li>
            <li>Select compliance level:
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Not met:</strong> Criterion is not currently met</li>
                    <li><strong>Partially met:</strong> Some aspects met, others not</li>
                    <li><strong>Fully met:</strong> Criterion is completely satisfied</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Provide <strong>evidence of compliance</strong> (links to documentation, examples, etc.)</li>
            <li>Add <strong>notes or explanations</strong></li>
            <li>Attach <strong>supporting documentation</strong> if needed</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Review your assessment for completeness</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit assessment</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing assessment history:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Functional standards</strong></li>
    <li>Select a product</li>
    <li>View the list of completed assessments</li>
    <li>Click on an assessment to view details</li>
    <li>Compare assessments over time to track compliance improvements</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Compliance reports:</h3>

<p>The functional standards section provides several reporting views:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Compliance summary:</strong> Overall compliance levels by standard</li>
    <li><strong>Gap analysis:</strong> Areas of non-compliance requiring attention</li>
    <li><strong>Product comparison:</strong> Compare compliance across products</li>
    <li><strong>Practice area breakdown:</strong> Compliance by practice area and theme</li>
    <li><strong>Evidence repository:</strong> Supporting evidence for assessments</li>
    <li><strong>Historical tracking:</strong> Progress over time</li>
</ul>

<div class="card border-primary mt-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h4 class="h6">Assessment tips</h4>
        <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>Be honest in your assessments - they help identify improvement areas</li>
            <li>Provide specific evidence rather than generic statements</li>
            <li>Reassess regularly (quarterly or when significant changes occur)</li>
            <li>Track improvement over time using historical assessments</li>
            <li>Use partial compliance to acknowledge progress while noting gaps</li>
            <li>Link evidence to specific documentation, tools, or practices in use</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="strategic-objectives">Strategic objectives</h2>

<p>Strategic objectives help align products, projects, and activities with organisational goals.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Working with strategic objectives:</h3>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="h6">Viewing objectives</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Strategic objectives</strong></li>
            <li>Browse the list of current strategic objectives</li>
            <li>Click on an objective to view details</li>
            <li>View linked products, projects, and RAID items</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h4 class="h6">Linking items to objectives</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>When creating or editing products, projects, risks, issues, actions, or milestones</li>
            <li>Find the <strong>Strategic objective</strong> dropdown</li>
            <li>Select the relevant objective</li>
            <li>Save your item</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Strategic objective details:</h3>

<p>The strategic objective details page shows:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Objective information:</strong> Name, description, owner, and status</li>
    <li><strong>Linked products:</strong> Products contributing to this objective</li>
    <li><strong>Linked projects:</strong> Projects aligned with this objective</li>
    <li><strong>Associated risks:</strong> Risks that could impact achievement</li>
    <li><strong>Related issues:</strong> Issues affecting progress</li>
    <li><strong>Supporting actions:</strong> Actions contributing to delivery</li>
    <li><strong>Key milestones:</strong> Milestones marking progress</li>
    <li><strong>Progress tracking:</strong> Overall progress percentage and status</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

